    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The curved, tooth-like shell of the dentalium mollusk, native to waters around British Columbia. Used as jewelry and as decoration for Native North American clothing; prior to the 20th century, also used as currency amongst California and Northwest Coast Native people.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
